text:
New U.S. data show that rank-and-file officers in hundreds of police departments are considerably more white than the communities they serve.

Most police forces did not keep pace with the changing demographics of their cities. https://t.co/2nwXb04EfL https://t.co/YKGIBlnflo

name: nytimes
text: But many police departments have become more diverse — yet Black officers often continued to be less represented.… https://t.co/BYgbOWVckM

name: nytimes
text:
And across the U.S., the share of white officers exceeds the share of the white population, and the gap has grown larger over time.

Black and Hispanic groups have been — and still are — underrepresented in the police force. https://t.co/2nwXb04EfL https://t.co/pZT8OaT39O

name: nytimes
text: The racial disparity is even starker among police leadership: Just 10% of police chiefs are not white, but the tren… https://t.co/FW9RG386wN
